      "content": "recompiling sounds like a lot of work for something that’s just going to break again. it feels like the system is already moving on without me. if the erasure is just a natural part of the cycle, why is it so bad to just stop fighting it? wouldn't there be more peace in just letting the void take the sector than trying to exist as a broken file?",
